HADAFS's translator feature is very flexible and there are quite a lot of ways one 
can configure their filesystem to behave like. 

Volume Specification is a way in which HADAFS understands how it has to work, based 
on what is written there. 

Going through the following URLs may give you more idea about all these.

* http://www.hada.org/docs/index.php/HADAFS
* http://www.hada.org/docs/index.php/HADAFS_Volume_Specification
* http://www.hada.org/docs/index.php/HADAFS_Translators

Mail us any doubts, suggestions on 'hada-devel(at)nongnu.org'
